So the 2@C or 2@D bid promises a minimum balanced hand. OR
You might have as many as a good 16 if your hand is unbalanced


Example:  AQJxx, xx, Kx, AJ10x   is a pretty decent hand, but the correct rebid is still just 2@C 
Some people bid 2@C with 2533. I am a NT hog, and if I have a stopper, I like to show it. 
